metadata_description: TikiTorch was named in homage to CACTUSTORCH by Vincent Yiu. The basic concept of CACTUSTORCH is that it spawns a new process. allocates a region of memory. writes shellcode into that region. and then uses CreateRemoteThread to execute said shellcode. Both the process and shellcode are specified by the user. The primary use case is as a JavaScript/VBScript loader via DotNetToJScript. which can be utilised in a variety of payload types such as HTA and VBA.

metadata_description: TikiTorch was named in homage to CACTUSTORCH by Vincent Yiu. The basic concept of CACTUSTORCH is that it spawns a new process. allocates a region of memory. writes shellcode into that region. and then uses CreateRemoteThread to execute said shellcode. Both the process and shellcode are specified by the user. The primary use case is as a JavaScript/VBScript loader via DotNetToJScript. which can be utilised in a variety of payload types such as HTA and VBA.

The basic concept of CACTUSTORCH is that it spawns a new process. allocates a region of memory. writes shellcode into that region. and then uses CreateRemoteThread to execute said shellcode. Both the process and shellcode are specified by the user. The primary use case is as a JavaScript/VBScript loader via DotNetToJScript. which can be utilised in a variety of payload types such as HTA and VBA.

metadata_description: TikiTorch was named in homage to CACTUSTORCH by Vincent Yiu. The basic concept of CACTUSTORCH is that it spawns a new process. allocates a region of memory. writes shellcode into that region. and then uses CreateRemoteThread to execute said shellcode. Both the process and shellcode are specified by the user. The primary use case is as a JavaScript/VBScript loader via DotNetToJScript. which can be utilised in a variety of payload types such as HTA and VBA.

metadata_description: TikiTorch was named in homage to CACTUSTORCH by Vincent Yiu. The basic concept of CACTUSTORCH is that it spawns a new process. allocates a region of memory. writes shellcode into that region. and then uses CreateRemoteThread to execute said shellcode. Both the process and shellcode are specified by the user. The primary use case is as a JavaScript/VBScript loader via DotNetToJScript. which can be utilised in a variety of payload types such as HTA and VBA.

The basic concept of CACTUSTORCH is that it spawns a new process. allocates a region of memory. writes shellcode into that region. and then uses CreateRemoteThread to execute said shellcode. Both the process and shellcode are specified by the user. The primary use case is as a JavaScript/VBScript loader via DotNetToJScript. which can be utilised in a variety of payload types such as HTA and VBA.

metadata_description: TikiTorch was named in homage to CACTUSTORCH by Vincent Yiu. The basic concept of CACTUSTORCH is that it spawns a new process. allocates a region of memory. writes shellcode into that region. and then uses CreateRemoteThread to execute said shellcode. Both the process and shellcode are specified by the user. The primary use case is as a JavaScript/VBScript loader via DotNetToJScript. which can be utilised in a variety of payload types such as HTA and VBA.

metadata_description: TikiTorch was named in homage to CACTUSTORCH by Vincent Yiu. The basic concept of CACTUSTORCH is that it spawns a new process. allocates a region of memory. writes shellcode into that region. and then uses CreateRemoteThread to execute said shellcode. Both the process and shellcode are specified by the user. The primary use case is as a JavaScript/VBScript loader via DotNetToJScript. which can be utilised in a variety of payload types such as HTA and VBA.

metadata_description: TikiTorch was named in homage to CACTUSTORCH by Vincent Yiu. The basic concept of CACTUSTORCH is that it spawns a new process. allocates a region of memory. writes shellcode into that region. and then uses CreateRemoteThread to execute said shellcode. Both the process and shellcode are specified by the user. The primary use case is as a JavaScript/VBScript loader via DotNetToJScript. which can be utilised in a variety of payload types such as HTA and VBA.

metadata_description: TikiTorch was named in homage to CACTUSTORCH by Vincent Yiu. The basic concept of CACTUSTORCH is that it spawns a new process. allocates a region of memory. writes shellcode into that region. and then uses CreateRemoteThread to execute said shellcode. Both the process and shellcode are specified by the user. The primary use case is as a JavaScript/VBScript loader via DotNetToJScript. which can be utilised in a variety of payload types such as HTA and VBA.

metadata_description: TikiTorch was named in homage to CACTUSTORCH by Vincent Yiu. The basic concept of CACTUSTORCH is that it spawns a new process. allocates a region of memory. writes shellcode into that region. and then uses CreateRemoteThread to execute said shellcode. Both the process and shellcode are specified by the user. The primary use case is as a JavaScript/VBScript loader via DotNetToJScript. which can be utilised in a variety of payload types such as HTA and VBA.
